        The primary root cause was an <strong>unindexed bulk UPDATE</strong> on the payment path
        (<span class="mono">SQL_ID ${rc.sqlId}</span>), which held long row-level locks in Oracle.
        This produced <strong>enq: TX — row lock contention</strong>, escalating to an
        <strong>ORA-00060 deadlock</strong> as UNDO usage reached ${d.systems.oracle.undo[d.peak]}%.
        Lock waits stalled MQ consumers on <span class="mono">PAYMENT.IN</span>, whose lag then
        exceeded the API timeout budget, surfacing as <strong>503 responses</strong> peaking at
        ${pct(rc.peak503)} on Checkout and Payment endpoints.
        <div class="callout">Maximum observed payment latency: <strong>${rc.maxLatency}s</strong>.
